added.title: Baby Hands
added.description: Robin has been hiding something under his gloves.

added.title: Body Adventure
added.description: When Cyborg is sick, Robin insists on shrinking to cell size to fight Cyborg's infection himself.

added.title: Vegetables
added.description: The Titans try vegetarianism, but learn that not everyone is cut out for that lifestyle.

added.title: Multiple Trick Pony
added.description: Robin insists he's a multiple trick pony.

added.title: Real Boy Adventures
added.description: When he transforms into "Fleshy Guy," Cyborg discovers the joy and pain of being human.

added.title: The Rival
added.description: The Wattersons look back on Anais' first days in the Watterson house. Gumball and Darwin quickly find themselves up an opponent who is able to outsmart them at every turn.

added.title: The Sucker
added.description: Gumball spends the day with Bomb Kid, who has decided Gumball is the perfect target for him and his friends to play pranks on. However he soon learns that Gumball is so gullible that pranks bounce off him.

added.title: The One
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are joking around, but when Tobias joins in and makes fun of Gumball, he's incredibly offended. They explain to Tobias that to make those jokes he'd need to be higher on Gumball's friend list. They think that's the end of it, but Tobias is after that number one spot.

added.title: The Cringe
added.description: When the uncomfortableness between them reaches new levels, Gumball and Hot Dog Guy decide they have to confront their ongoing awkwardness by making things as awkward as possible.

added.title: The Faith
added.description: Everything in Elmore is suddenly just various shades of grey, and things all over town are going wrong. Gumball and Darwin follow the mayhem and learn that one person was holding the whole town together: Alan. They have to restore his faith in the world to bring color back to Elmore.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part I
added.description: When mysterious circumstances cause issues at the Trading Tree, Craig tries to save the day!

added.title: Capture The Flag Part II
added.description: The Creek gets help from an unlikely friend.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part III
added.description: Craig goes in search of answers, and finds a legend.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part IV
added.description: Craig puts a plan into motion to save the Creek.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part V
added.description: It all comes down to this, the fate of the Creek is at stake!

added.title: Look Who's Clocking
added.description: When Harold's warnings not to mess with the clock go ignored, the kids are forced to save themselves when Duncan tears a hole in the fabric of time.

added.title: Harold Swatter and the Goblet of Flies
added.description: After finding what he believes to be a magic wand, Owen accidentally turns Harold into a housefly.

added.title: Stink. Stank. Stunk
added.description: When a skunk comes seeking its annual revenge on Chef, Duncan sees it as an opportunity to get a vacation from daycare.

added.title: Baby Pepito
added.description: When a mysterious "baby" appears on Chata's doorstep, V&V are convinced it's not what it seems.

added.title: Cenote Seekers
added.description: When Vic and Val are running too late to get a ride from Xochi to a fun water park cenote on a particularly hot day, they instead take their bikes. But they wind up lost in the desert and start to hallucinate while blaming each other for getting into this mess.

added.title: My Thirsty Little Monster
added.description: When Valentino discovers Victor has been hiding a baby vampire bat in the house, Victor must convince his brother that he can handle having a pet.

added.title: La Planchada
added.description: When Vic gets the chicken pox and is forbidden from playing in a tag tournament, he summons a mythical ghost nurse to cure him.

added.title: Tez Breaks Bread
added.description: When Tez returns to town and invites Chata and the boys to a dinner party, she insists they attend so Victor and Valentino set out to expose him as the evil magician he truly is.

added.title: Slobbery
added.description: Burger's roommate is not only a problem for him, but for Apple and Onion who need Burger's help for something else.

added.title: Microwave's Dance Club
added.description: DJ Saltfish and MC Ackee are in town for two nights only and Apple and Onion are determined to make the most of it and bust some moves on the dance floor.

added.title: All Work and No Play
added.description: Having finally saved up and aquired an expensive toy race track, Apple and Onion are faced with one problem- there is no time to play with it.

added.title: Players of the Lost Park
added.description: When Team Tennyson visits Raspberry Park for some R & R, they get more than they bargained for. What they think are innocent games of chance are a revenge plot by Zombozo to steal the Rustbuggy and rob Team Tennyson!

added.title: De-Fanged!
added.description: Team Tennyson travels to the new Laser Town VR, but when Kevin cheats his way to the top, Ben must team up with former champ Fang if he is going to defeat his souped-up rival.

added.title: Mock 10
added.description: Ben, Kevin and La Grange find themselves stuck 'outside of time' after the latter hijacks a supersonic train with a faulty engine, forcing the trio to team up and slow down.

added.title: Rekoil
added.description: As Team Tennyson fights to stop Dr. Animo from raiding an animal shelter, Ben faces one villain more than he bargained for, King Koil, now Animo's pet.

added.title: Buktu The Future
added.description: After Tim Buktu's live stream is mysteriously cut short, Team Tennyson must attempt a rescue mission and break inside the highly confidential Area 55 in order to save him.

added.title: Developing Dilemna
added.description: Frankie lets Elliott get a pet, which doesn't go down well with their new neighbor.

added.title: Inadvertant Inversion
added.description: As Elliott, Mo and Frankie all try something new at the Hive, they find their worlds are about to be turned upside down again.

added.title: #Retreat!
added.description: Jessica Cruz and some super friends go on an overnight camping trip without their powers and are attacked by Poison Ivy and a horde of Plant Zombies!

added.title: #DinnerForFive
added.description: Barbara Gordon finds herself in a tight spot when an awkward dinner with a new friend's father turns into something so much more.

added.title: #LivingTheNightmare
added.description: When Zee's friends are held captive in their nightmares by a dream demon, she'll have to confront her own hidden insecurities, or risk the Super Hero Girls being trapped in a prison of their own fears forever.

added.title: #AllAboutZee
added.description: Zee Zatara is flattered when she meets an overeager admirer named Casey Krinsky, but soon realizes that "her biggest fan" wants much more than just an autograph.

added.title: #TweenTitans
added.description: Jessica Cruz is hired by billionaire playboy Bruce Wayne to chaperone young Dick Grayson's Metropolis birthday bash and brings Karen Beecher along to help, but the girls get more than they bargained for when the TWEEN party guests reveal their TITANic personalities.

added.title: Captain Craboo
added.description: The Bears are reunited with their pet crab, Captain Craboo. But after an unfortunate run-in with Nom Nom, the Bears may lose their pet forever.

added.title: Yuri and the Bear
added.description: Baby Ice Bear lives alone in the arctic and meets a mysterious man named Yuri. Together they help each other survive the cold environment.

added.title: Icy Nights
added.description: Ice Bear rides his custom vacuum into the city. But when a gang of techies steal the vacuum, Ice Bear goes on a rescue mission that takes him through the underground world of the city.

added.title: Everyone's Tube
added.description: Through a standard video browsing session online, we get a glimpse of the different kinds of videos the Bears have posted.

added.title: Creature Mysteries
added.description: Ranger Tabes tells the Bears she's been investigating a mysterious creature. But when the Bears realize she's actually investigating their friend Charlie, they split up to ensure Charlie's safety.

added.title: Sir Tree House
added.description: Sir Tree is lonely, so Seth builds a treehouse in his branches to keep him company. It's such a hit, soon all of Fungietown moves in! But when the added weight strains Sir Tree, can Seth convince him to take better care of himself?

added.title: Lord Clawly Caper
added.description: When his medals are stolen during a Fungietown school assembly, Seth and Claudette start an investigation to find the culprit before everyone is thrown into the Triloknight's dungeon!

added.title: Restaurant Wars
added.description: Steven must help the Frymans and the Pizzas settle a reignited rivalry between their restaurants.

added.title: Kiki's Pizza Delivery Service
added.description: Steven saves Kiki from some delicious nightmares.

added.title: Monster Reunion
added.description: Steven reunites with an old friend.

added.title: Alone at Sea
added.description: Steven and Greg take a boat trip out to sea and find themselves in dangerous water.

added.title: Greg the Babysitter
added.description: Steven learns the tale of how Greg came to work at the car wash.

added.title: Schnorp
added.description: The Thunderkittens plug a new video game cartridge into Snarf only to learn that it didn't load a game, it loaded a whole new personality into their pal! Meet Schnorp, a kind Swedish man who loves the beauty of nature and collecting berries! Schnorp is loads of fun, but we're gonna want Snarf back, right?

added.title: Berb-cules
added.description: The ThunderCats finally sit the Berbils down and tell them they really shouldn't be building things for the Mutants anymore, it's time for the Berbils to stand up for themselves. The Berbils take this advice way too far and build a giant, building-sized, Berbil named Berbcules. Berb-cules takes back everything the Berbils ever built for the Mutants and everything they ever built for the ThunderCats! Now Panthro has to figure out a way to a defeat the most powerful invention the best little builders have ever built!

added.title: Pumm-Ra
added.description: Mumm-Ra plans to disguise himself as a Thunderian and infiltrate Cats' Lair, but the Ancient Spirits of Evil are mad at him and won't give him any magic today. No matter, Mumm-Ra knows what a ThunderCat looks like so he slaps on some awful, unconvincing, cat make up and heads to Cats' Lair to introduce himself!

added.title: King of the Machines
added.description: Panthro gets insecure when he finds out Barbastella has a history of dating royalty, so he tries to impress her by becoming "King of the Machines" and giving all the appliances in the Cats' Lair artificial intelligence.

added.title: Mandora Saves Christmas
added.description: Santa Claus is on the run from Mandora! Can the Thundercats help him get off Third Earth without getting caught? And can Santa Claus teach them a little something about this weird new holiday "Christmas"?

added.title: The Belly of the Beast
added.description: To repair the Land-Bounty, the ninja must retrieve a critical engine component that has been swallowed by a giant scarab beetle.

added.title: Booby-Traps, and How To Survive Them
added.description: The ninja team up with a reluctant Clutch Powers to enter a mysterious pyramid where they inadvertently unleash an ancient evil.

added.title: The News Never Sleeps!
added.description: Lil' Nelson takes a job as a paperboy, which is more difficult than it sounds in a city overrun by scorching Pyro Vipers and an evil Serpentine sorceress.

added.title: Ninja vs. Lava
added.description: The ninja find themselves trapped in a pyramid and must escape encroaching lava to warn NINJAGO City of a new Serpentine invasion.

added.title: Snaketastrophy
added.description: The Serpentine attack on NINJAGO City is seen from an unexpected perspective - entirely in the style of a live newscast delivered by Gayle Gossip and her cameraman.

added.title: Flyaway
added.description: When Adorabat's spirit transcends her body during a meditation exercise, Mao Mao and Badgerclops have to figure out a way to return her to the real world.

added.title: Baost in Show
added.description: When Bao Bao returns, and the King makes him his pet, Mao Mao must rescue his ex-partner.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: From Below
added.description: Axel juggles looking after Luka and defending the house from Dr. Nautilus's latest abomination, a tentacle monster that attacks from every drain, pipe, and faucet in the building!

added.title: Winner Takes All
added.description: After months of training for Luchador Day, Axel needs Masko to coach him against a pair of uninvited competitors - Madcap and Dynamo!

added.title: Prepare for the Worst
added.description: Axel and Bobbie Blobby skip out on Sarge's disaster-prep drills, leaving enough of a gap in the team's defenses for a crow to swoop in and snatch Sarge! Feeling responsible, Axel leads the team on a search-and-rescue mission.

added.title: Stuck on You
added.description: Tired of Axel and the team taking him for granted, Masko tries to get kidnapped and ends up stuck to Dynamo, who's less than enthused with his rubbery new sidekick.

added.title: Opposites Attract
added.description: Claiming he's good at heart, Dynamo convinces Axel and the team to help him find a battery that can power his centrifuge and free him from Madtrap's control - but Bobbie Blobby isn't buying the baddie's story.

added.title: The Throw Down/Brawl for It All
added.description: The Throw Down: Lightning reveals his discovery of the Mind Core Cell but the AO arrive only to discover that Magnus has already beaten them to it./Brawl for It All: With both team's Bakugan knocked into a hibernation state by the Mind Core Cell only Dan and Magnus remain locked in a brawl for it all!

added.title: Career Opportunities/Punch the Clock
added.description: Career Opportunities: After defeating Magnus the AO get an offer of employment from a surprising source Philomena Dusk!/Punch the Clock: During a commercial to celebrate their joining the AAAnimus team Dan and the AO rebel before they sellout.

added.title: High Flying Hostiles/Backfire Brawl
added.description: High Flying Hostiles: While escorting the Mind Core Cell to AAAnimus Campus, the AO are attacked by Masato Kazami and his Body Guards./Backfire Brawl: Philomena's attempt to refocus the Mind Core Cell's power backfires and the AO must fight their fellow employees inside the AAAnimus Campus.

added.title: Hostile Take Over/The Big Bounce
added.description: Hostile Take Over: After more unsuccessful attempts to harness Core Cell energy the AO must battle their own Bakugan with AAAnimus tech in order to save them./The Big Bounce: The AO confront Philomena with concerns about her control over the Core Cell energy and are fired in the most unceremonious of manners.

added.title: Awesome vs. AAAnimus
added.description: Awesome V Aaanimus, Part 1: The AO plan on sneaking into AAAnimus and rescuing their Bakugan but are stopped by Benton who offers up an alternate plan./Awesome V Aaanimus, Part 2: The AO team up with Benton Dusk to recapture their stolen Bakugan and free the energy from the Mind Core Cell under the control of AAAnimus.

added.title: The Escape Room of Doom
added.description: The gang infiltrate an escape room game center to thwart Score Creeper, but their former foe claims he only works there to pay the bills.

added.title: Last One There
added.description: When Unikitty accidentally invokes an ancient curse, the gang must beat Master Frown and Brock back to the castle before one of them literally turns into a rotten egg.

added.title: The Very Best Candy
added.description: The gang can't decide which of their candy is the best, so they turn it sentient and have it fight to determine the winner.

added.title: The Unikingdom Awards
added.description: Unikitty throws an elaborate award show for everyone in the Unikingdom, including Master Frown and Brock, but tensions rise when Frown fails to win an award.

added.title: The Birthday to End All Birthdays
added.description:
Unikitty and the gang secretly throw Master Frown the birthday of his dreams, but their efforts have lasting repercussions beyond Frown's special day./
Following the events of Master Frown's birthday, Unikitty and her friends form a resistance group to restore the Unikingdom.

added.title: Red Action 3: Grudgement Day
added.description: KO and Enid attempt to prevent a mysterious power battle between Rad and Red Action.

added.title: Carl
added.description: A pleasant weekend goes awry when a monster attacks.

added.title: Dendy's Video Channel
added.description: Dendy tries to update KO's Video Channel for him, but has trouble finding something to post.

added.title: Let's Fight to the End
added.description: When a fighting tournament is announced at the Plaza, there is more at stake than meets the eye.

added.title: Thank You for Watching the Show
added.description: When KO finds moments of his life slipping by, he begins to suspect something weird is going on.

added.title: Frenemy
added.description: When the coolest girl in school befriends the girls, she charms them into becoming her accomplices in a series of adventurous crimes.

added.title: Once Upon a Townsville
added.description: When a dainty princess on a mission comes to Townsville, the girls must learn the superhero way isn't always the right way.

added.title: Man Up 2: Still Man-ing
added.description: When someone steals all the water in Townsville, it's up to the girls to race through the Townsville Wastelands to get it back.

added.title: Viral Spiral
added.description: When the Amoeba Boys wreak havoc on the internet, Bubbles has to hack her sisters in to stop them.

added.title: Bubbles of the Opera
added.description: When Bubbles gets a bad school photo, it sends her into an existential tailspin of darkness.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 2
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Perfect Day
added.description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

added.title: Don't Drink the Water
added.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

added.title: And Then There Were None
added.description: Vilgax and Eon team up to wipe out every Ben in every dimension!

added.title: The Vengers
added.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: No Honor Among Bros
added.description: Rook is under the influence of Fistrick's "bro" essence, and starts to act like a bro. Can he and Ben infiltrate an alien fight club to claim the Golden Fist? (Introducing Slix Vigma, alien promoter.)

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: Elements Part 2: Bespoken For
added.description: Ice King weaves a tale filled with drama, romance, and men's fashion.

added.title: Elements Part 4: Cloudy
added.description: Before they can restore Ooo, Finn and Jake will have to escape exile in an endless sky.

added.title: Elements Part 5: Slime Central
added.description: Finn and Jake infiltrate the new Slime Kingdom and are drawn into a heated skate battle.

added.title: Elements Part 6: Happy Warrior
added.description: One step closer to success, Finn and his friends fight through a new, more brutal, Fire Kingdom to find Flame Princess.

added.title: Elements Part 8: Skyhooks II
added.description: With time running out, Finn and Lumpy Space Princess work together to unlock one of Ooo's greatest secrets.

added.title: El Rival
added.description: Volvemos a la época en la que Anaís era una bebé recién nacida, y los celos de Gumball y Darwin desatan una guerra de bebés.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Tonto
added.description: Darwin termina en la sala de detención con el Chico Bomba, que decide convertir a Darwin en su nuevo blanco. Sin embargo, el ataque se vuelve en su contra cuando Darwin le arruina la vida.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Elegido
added.description: Tobías intenta ser el mejor amigo de Gumball.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Incomodidad
added.description: Gumball y Chico Salchicha descubren por qué se sienten tan incómodos el uno con el otro.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Fe
added.description: Alan perdió su fe en la humanidad y puso el mundo blanco y negro. Gumball tiene que superar el odio que siente hacia Alan para recuperar el color a través del canto.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: World's Best Boss
added.description: The park guys want to give Benson a World's Best Boss mug.

added.title: Last Meal
added.description: Muscle Man wants to eat his favorite foods before going on a diet.

added.title: Sleep Fighter
added.description: The park guys have to help Muscle Man stop fighting in his sleep.

added.title: Party Re-Pete
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to save Benson from an evil party company.

added.title: Steak Me Amadeus
added.description: Mordecai wants to ask Margaret to be his girlfriend.

added.title: In the Clouds
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a boy get his head out of the clouds and focused on his history test.

added.title: The Lepre-Con
added.description: On a St. Patrick's Day trip to Ireland, Uncle Grandpa and the gang cross paths with a sneaky leprechaun.

added.title: Uncle Fashion
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a young boy who wants to be a fashion designer by taking him somewhere his style will be appreciated.

added.title: G'day Mornin'
added.description: Uncle grandpa goes to Australia where he must stop an out-of-control collecting kangaroo before he destroys the Earth.

added.title: Fear of Flying
added.description: Uncle grandpa helps a young boy overcome his fear of flying.

added.title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
added.description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

added.title: El Vientre del Monstruo
added.description: Para reparar el Land-Bounty, el ninja debe recuperar un componente crítico del motor que ha sido tragado por un escarabajo gigante.

added.title: Trampas y Como Sobrevivir a Ellas
added.description: El ninja se une a un clutch Powers renuente para entrar en una misteriosa pirámide donde desatan sin darse cuenta un antiguo mal.

added.title: Las Noticias Nunca Duermen
added.description: Lil 'Nelson toma un trabajo como repartidor de periódicos, lo cual es más difícil de lo que parece en una ciudad invadida por Pyro Vipers y una malvada hechicera serpentina.

added.title: Ninja Contra Lava
added.description: Los ninja se encuentran atrapados en una pirámide y deben escapar de la lava invasora para advertir a la ciudad de NINJAGO de una nueva invasión serpentina.

added.title: Serpientastrofe
added.description: El ataque de Serpentine en NINJAGO City se ve desde una perspectiva inesperada, completamente al estilo de un noticiero en vivo entregado por Gayle Gossip y su camarógrafo.

added.title: #Retirada
added.description: Jessica Cruz y algunas de sus mejores amigas salen a pasar una noche de campamento sin sus poderes, iy son atacadas por Hiedra Venenosa y una horda de plantas zombis!
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #CenaParaCinco
added.description: Barbara Gordon está en apuros cuando una cena incómoda el padre de una nueva amiga, se convierte en algo muy diferente.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Straight Illin
added.description: In an escalating series of dares, Clarence eats five hundred hard-boiled eggs, delighting the kids around him. As Clarence grows sicker and sicker, the kids get more and more grossed out until they want nothing to do with him.

added.title: Un Gran Enfrentamiento
added.description: Lightning por fin revela la ubicación de la Célula Núcleo, pero cuando Los Fantásticos llegan, descubren que Magnus fue más rápido que ellos.

added.title: La Batalla Decisiva
added.description: Luego de que la Célula Núcleo pusiera en estado de hibernación a los Bakugan de ambos equipos, Dan y Magnus se encuentran atrapados en una batalla donde lo apostarán todo.

added.title: Water Park
added.description: The trio heads to Squirty's Moist Mountain water park, and as Clarence learns the truth about his idol Squirty, Jeff and Sumo wait in line for the reopening of the parks tallest slide, The Curd Churner.

added.title: Oportunidades Laborales
added.description: Después de derrotar a Magnus, los Fantásticos reciben una oferta de empleo de alguien inesperado... Filomena Dusk.

added.title: Un Nuevo Empleo
added.description: Durante un comercial para celebrar su contrato con el equipo AAAnimus, Dan y Los Fantásticos deciden rebelarse antes que traicionar sus principios.

added.title: Breehn Ho
added.description: Avast mateys! Clarence and Sumo are psyched to play their pirate-themed board game, Thirty Days and Seven Seas, until they learn Jeff has invited boring old Breehn along. After Breehn gets frustrated and leaves, it's up to the three scallywags to rescue Breehn from an intense flood.

added.title: Enemigos en el Aire
added.description: Cuando Los Fantásticos transportan la Célula Núcleo a las instalaciones de AAAnimus, son atacados por Masato Kazami y sus Guardaespaldas.

added.title: Un Experimento Fallido
added.description: El plan de Filomena Dusk para redireccionar la energía de la Célula Núcleo fracasa, y Los Fantásticos deben pelear contra sus propios compañeros de trabajo dentro de las instalaciones de AAAnimus.

added.title: Perdiendo el Control
added.description: Después de más intentos fallidos por aprovechar la energía la Célula núcleo, Los Fantásticos deben pelear contra sus propios Bakugan usando tecnología AAAnimus para salvarlos.

added.title: Despedidos
added.description: Los Fantásticos confrontan a Filomena, preocupados de que ella controle la energía de la Célula núcleo, y son despedidos de una forma poco profesional.

added.title: Balance
added.description: Ms. Baker introduces a new student, a short little kid with a hook for a hand named Balance. Clarence is pumped to have a new friend, despite Balance's gruff attitude and snarky jibes at the other kids. When Clarence discovers a disturbing secret about Balance, he and Belson team up to expose him for who he truly is.

added.title: Fantasticos vs. AAAnimus Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos planean infiltrarse a AAAnimus para rescatar a sus Bakugan, pero Benton los detiene para ofrecerles un plan alternativo.

added.title: Fantasticos vs. AAAnimus Parte 2
added.description: Los Fantásticos unen fuerzas con Benton Dusk para rescatar a sus Bakugan y liberar la energía de la Célula Núcleo que AAAnimus tiene bajo su control.

added.title: El Ganador se lo Lleva Todo
added.description: Después de meses de entrenamiento para el Día del Luchador, Axel necesita que Masko lo entrene contra un par de competidores no invitados: iMadcap y Dynamo!

added.title: Presumir en el Concurso
added.description: Cuando Bao Bao regresa y el rey lo convierte en su mascota, Mao Mao debe rescatar a su antiguo compañero.

added.title: Suelta
added.description: Cuando el espíritu de Adorabat trasciende su cuerpo durante un ejercicio de meditación, Mao Mao y Colosal tienen que descubrir un modo de devolverla al mundo real.

added.title: Preparense Para Lo Peor
added.description: iAxel y Bobbie Blobby se saltan los simulacros de preparación para desastres de Sarge, dejando suficiente espacio en las defensas del equipo para que un cuervo se precipite y arrebata a Sarge! Sintiéndose responsable, Axel lidera al equipo en una misión de búsqueda y rescate.

added.title: Bismuto Casual
added.description: Perla invita a Bismuto a la pista de patinaje para darle una lección sobre cómo forjar relaciones humanas.

added.title: Pegado a Ti
added.description: Cansado de que Axel y el equipo lo den por sentado, Masko intenta ser secuestrado y termina atrapado en Dynamo, que está menos que entusiasmado con su nuevo compañero de goma.

added.title: Desde las Profundidades
